value="<b>Design Deep Dive</b><div>From the simple design we can see we have services1 ... serviceN. These services&nbsp;</div><div>can be micro-services that deal with different scenarios. We might have a service&nbsp;</div><div>that informs our customers of the stock of a product they have been waiting for, and&nbsp;</div><div>another service can send notification when an item they bought from our online store</div><div>is shipped and when it will be delivered to them.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>However, this system have couple of flows:&nbsp;</div><div>1. Single point of failure. Imagine if the notification system&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="background-color: initial;">is down. That means no</span></div><div><span style="background-color: initial;">&nbsp; &nbsp; notification will be sent to any of the platforms we support.</span></div><div><span style="background-color: initial;">2. It is hard to scale. The notification system handles everything. We want the ability</span></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; to scale databases and caches independently.&nbsp;</div><div><span style="background-color: initial;">3. Bottlenecks. Notification systems are resource intensive. So, that means one&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="background-color: initial;">&nbsp; &nbsp; system will become resource constrained.&nbsp;</span></div>" div.div: From the simple design we can see we have services1 ... serviceN. These services
can be micro-services that deal with different scenarios. We might have a service
that informs our customers of the stock of a product they have been waiting for, and
another service can send notification when an item they bought from our online store
is shipped and when it will be delivered to them.
However, this system have couple of flows:
1. Single point of failure. Imagine if the notification system is down. That means no

div.span: notification will be sent to any of the platforms we support.
2. It is hard to scale. The notification system handles everything. We want the ability

div.div: to scale databases and caches independently.
